---
title: ADR-021 — Constraint-Floor Search: Single Round-Trip Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as Analyst (Mode 3)
    participant F as ControlPlaneColumn Form 3
    participant API as POST /constraint-floor-search
    participant BS as Binary Search (backend)
    participant Eng as Simulation Engine

    U->>F: Click "Find safe boundary"
    activate F
    F->>F: Show PENDING spinner
    F->>API: POST {focal_cohort_index: 0, lo: 0.1, hi: 3.0, tolerance: 0.01}
    activate API
    API->>BS: binary_search(scenario, focal_cohort, lo, hi, tol)
    activate BS

    loop O(log₂(n)) evaluations ≈ 8–9 iterations
        BS->>Eng: run_trajectory(fiscal_multiplier=mid)
        Eng-->>BS: crosses_floor? (True/False)
        BS->>BS: adjust lo or hi
    end

    BS-->>API: ConstraintFloorSearchResponse{status, boundary, uncertainty_lo, uncertainty_hi, evaluations}
    deactivate BS
    API-->>F: 200 OK + response body
    deactivate API
    F->>F: Render result (FOUND / NOT_FOUND / ERROR)
    F-->>U: "fiscal multiplier ≥ 1.18 (±0.01)  |  9 evaluations  ·  [0.1, 3.0] searched"
    deactivate F

    note over U,Eng: Single HTTP round trip replaces O(n) sequential /branch calls.<br/>Analyst cites specific boundary value at negotiating table.
